        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 6:29PM EDT until July 8 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Almeda
Intersection, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Varnville, Cummings, Almeda Intersection, Early Branch, Camp
Branch, Fechtig, Nixville and Stafford.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.

Report severe weather to your nearest law enforcement agency or the
National Weather Service office in Charleston SC.

Report damage directly to the Charleston National Weather Service at
888-383-2024 when it is safe to do so.</instruction>
